CREATED:20260326T185027Z
DESCRIPTION:Dear Faculty\,\n\nWe invite you to join in on conversations to
  discuss a key pedagogical issue: Teaching Writing in the Age of AI. \n\n
 Teaching Writing in the Age of AI sessions will bring together small grou
 ps of faculty from across the university to explore the challenges and op
 portunities of designing writing assignments and teaching with writing in
  an era of artificial intelligence. In collaboration with the Office of U
 ndergraduate Education and Trinity College Undergraduate Education\, thes
 e conversations facilitated by faculty from the Thompson Writing Program 
 respond to a growing concern: that undergraduates are writing less\, or o
 nly under timed conditions\, at the expense of their long-term developmen
 t as writers. Each 60-minute session is designed as a supported community
  conversation\, a space for faculty to think through practical approaches
  to writing pedagogy together\, across disciplines. Join us for one of ou
 r conversations this spring\, featuring small groups of faculty\, lunch\,
  and the kind of frank discussion that helps us all teach better.\n\nRegi
 ster Here: https://duke.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_cx3eGgvscbVPbIG
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260409T130000
